trans-unit.source: validation_steps: Only relevant if validation_data is provided and is a tf.data dataset. Total number of steps (batches of samples) to draw before stopping when performing validation at the end of every epoch. If 'validation_steps' is None, validation will run until the validation_data dataset is exhausted. In the case of a infinite dataset, it will run into a infinite loop. trans-unit.source: BackupAndRestore callback is intended to recover from interruptions that happened in the middle of a model.fit execution by backing up the training states in a temporary checkpoint file (based on TF CheckpointManager) at the end of each epoch. If training restarted before completion, the training state and model are restored to the most recently saved state at the beginning of a new model.fit() run. Note that user is responsible to bring jobs back up. This callback is important for the backup and restore mechanism for fault tolerance purpose. And the model to be restored from an previous checkpoint is expected to be the same as the one used to back up. If user changes arguments passed to compile or fit, the checkpoint saved for fault tolerance can become invalid.
trans-unit.target: BackupAndRestore 回调旨在通过在每个时期结束时将训练状态备份到临时检查点文件（基于TF CheckpointManager）中来恢复在model.fit执行过程中发生的中断。如果训练在完成之前重新开始，则训练状态和模型将在新model.fit（）运行开始时恢复到最近保存的状态。请注意，用户有责任备份作业。此回调对于出于容错目的的备份和还原机制很重要。从上一个检查点还原的模型应该与用于备份的模型相同。如果用户更改传递给编译或调整的参数，则为容错而保存的检查点可能变为无效。

trans-unit.source: grad_fn is a function with the signature g(*grad_ys) which returns a list of Tensors - the derivatives of Tensors in y with respect to the Tensors in x. grad_ys is a Tensor or sequence of Tensors the same size as y holding the initial value gradients for each Tensor in y. In a pure mathematical sense, a vector-argument vector-valued function f's derivatives should be its Jacobian matrix J. Here we are expressing the Jacobian J as a function grad_fn which defines how J will transform a vector grad_ys when left-multiplied with it (grad_ys * J).
